title: Qu'est-ce Que Je Disais
provenance_text:
James L. Winokur, Pittsburgh, PA, by November 1968 [1]; 

Notes:
[1]. The Winokurs lend the sculpture (no. 66) to the exhibition "Sculpture We Live with: Privately Owned in the Pittsburgh Area" held at the Museum of Art, Carnegie Institute, November 1968 - January 1969.

The watercolor was accessioned as a 1977 year-end partial gift on February 9, 1978. It was received at the museum on May 13, 1985. Committee action on completion of the gift as a 1985 year-end gift was taken on February 6, 1986.

Updated and under review by CGK.
